content: and YSA liaison offices help to maintain public safety on the Forest Moon of Kodia III by working closely with the rangers to address any potential threats or criminal activities. Their presence allows for a more proactive approach to ensuring the safety and security of both the local population and the visiting researchers, tourists, and other personnel on the moon. By working together, the rangers, YNP, and YSA can create a safer environment for everyone involved in the conservation and exploration efforts on Kodia III.
